CONTEXT:
QUILTA currently has all code in one App.tsx file (2000+ lines). Need to refactor into modular architecture with proper routing and state management.

TASK: Implement Week 2 architectural improvements.

## DAY 8-10: SPLIT INTO FEATURE MODULES

Restructure the codebase:
src/
├── features/
│   ├── auth/
│   │   ├── components/
│   │   │   └── AuthView.tsx
│   │   └── hooks/
│   │       └── useAuth.ts
│   ├── projects/
│   │   ├── components/
│   │   │   ├── ProjectsView.tsx
│   │   │   ├── ProjectCard.tsx
│   │   │   ├── CreateProjectView.tsx
│   │   │   ├── EditProjectView.tsx
│   │   │   └── ProjectDetailView.tsx
│   │   └── hooks/
│   │       └── useProjects.ts
│   ├── interviews/
│   │   ├── components/
│   │   │   ├── InterviewDetailView.tsx
│   │   │   ├── RecordInterviewView.tsx
│   │   │   └── InterviewCard.tsx
│   │   └── hooks/
│   │       └── useInterviews.ts
│   ├── coding/
│   │   ├── components/
│   │   │   ├── CodingView.tsx
│   │   │   ├── CodeSelectionModal.tsx
│   │   │   └── GranularHighlighter.tsx
│   │   └── hooks/
│   │       ├── useCoding.ts
│   │       └── useTextSelection.ts
│   └── export/
│       ├── components/
│       │   └── ExportView.tsx
│       └── hooks/
│           └── useExport.ts
├── shared/
│   ├── components/
│   │   ├── Layout.tsx
│   │   ├── ConfirmDialog.tsx
│   │   └── LoadingStates.tsx
│   └── hooks/
│       └── useConfirm.ts
├── services/
│   ├── dbService.ts
│   └── geminiService.ts
├── lib/
│   └── toast.ts
├── types.ts
├── constants.ts
└── App.tsx (now just routing)

1. Extract each view component into its feature folder
2. Create custom hooks for each feature's logic
3. Move shared components to shared/
4. Keep services/ as is

Example hook pattern - `features/projects/hooks/useProjects.ts`:
```typescript
import { useState, useEffect } from 'react';
import { dbService } from '../../../services/dbService';
import { Project } from '../../../types';

export const useProjects = () => {
  const [projects, setProjects] = useState<Project[]>([]);
  const [isLoading, setIsLoading] = useState(true);

  useEffect(() => {
    loadProjects();
  }, []);

  const loadProjects = () => {
    setIsLoading(true);
    const data = dbService.getProjects();
    setProjects(data);
    setTimeout(() => setIsLoading(false), 300);
  };

  const createProject = (title: string, description: string) => {
    const project = dbService.createProject(title, description);
    setProjects(prev => [...prev, project]);
    return project;
  };

  const updateProject = (id: string, title: string, description: string) => {
    const updated = dbService.updateProject(id, title, description);
    setProjects(prev => prev.map(p => p.id === id ? updated : p));
    return updated;
  };

  return {
    projects,
    isLoading,
    createProject,
    updateProject,
    refresh: loadProjects,
  };
};
```

## DAY 11-12: ADD REACT ROUTER

Install React Router:
```bash
npm install react-router-dom
```

1. Create `src/routes.tsx`:
```typescript
import { createBrowserRouter } from 'react-router-dom';
import AuthView from './features/auth/components/AuthView';
import ProjectsView from './features/projects/components/ProjectsView';
import ProjectDetailView from './features/projects/components/ProjectDetailView';
import CreateProjectView from './features/projects/components/CreateProjectView';
import InterviewDetailView from './features/interviews/components/InterviewDetailView';
import RecordInterviewView from './features/interviews/components/RecordInterviewView';
import CodingView from './features/coding/components/CodingView';
import ExportView from './features/export/components/ExportView';

export const router = createBrowserRouter([
  {
    path: '/',
    element: <AuthView />,
  },
  {
    path: '/projects',
    element: <ProjectsView />,
  },
  {
    path: '/projects/new',
    element: <CreateProjectView />,
  },
  {
    path: '/projects/:projectId',
    element: <ProjectDetailView />,
  },
  {
    path: '/projects/:projectId/interviews/new',
    element: <RecordInterviewView />,
  },
  {
    path: '/projects/:projectId/interviews/:interviewId',
    element: <InterviewDetailView />,
  },
  {
    path: '/projects/:projectId/interviews/:interviewId/coding',
    element: <CodingView />,
  },
  {
    path: '/projects/:projectId/export',
    element: <ExportView />,
  },
]);
```

2. Update App.tsx to use router:
```typescript
import { RouterProvider } from 'react-router-dom';
import { router } from './routes';
import { Toaster } from 'react-hot-toast';

function App() {
  return (
    <>
      <Toaster position="top-right" />
      <RouterProvider router={router} />
    </>
  );
}

export default App;
```

3. Update all components to use routing:
Replace `onBack={() => setView('PROJECTS')}` with:
```typescript
import { useNavigate } from 'react-router-dom';

const navigate = useNavigate();
// Use: navigate('/projects')
```

Replace `onOpen={(p) => openProject(p)}` with:
```typescript
navigate(`/projects/${p.id}`)
```

4. Use params in detail views:
```typescript
import { useParams } from 'react-router-dom';

const { projectId, interviewId } = useParams();
```

## DAY 13-14: CLEAN UP STATE MANAGEMENT

1. Create `src/contexts/AppContext.tsx`:
```typescript
import React, { createContext, useContext, useState, ReactNode } from 'react';
import { Profile } from '../types';
import { dbService } from '../services/dbService';

interface AppContextType {
  user: Profile | null;
  login: (email: string) => void;
  logout: () => void;
}

const AppContext = createContext<AppContextType | undefined>(undefined);

export const AppProvider: React.FC<{ children: ReactNode }> = ({ children }) => {
  const [user, setUser] = useState<Profile | null>(dbService.getCurrentUser());

  const login = (email: string) => {
    const profile = dbService.login(email);
    setUser(profile);
  };

  const logout = () => {
    dbService.logout();
    setUser(null);
  };

  return (
    <AppContext.Provider value={{ user, login, logout }}>
      {children}
    </AppContext.Provider>
  );
};

export const useApp = () => {
  const context = useContext(AppContext);
  if (!context) throw new Error('useApp must be used within AppProvider');
  return context;
};
```

2. Wrap App with providers in main.tsx:
```typescript
import { AppProvider } from './contexts/AppContext';

ReactDOM.createRoot(document.getElementById('root')!).render(
  <React.StrictMode>
    <AppProvider>
      <App />
    </AppProvider>
  </React.StrictMode>
);
```

3. Add protected route wrapper:
Create `src/components/ProtectedRoute.tsx`:
```typescript
import { Navigate } from 'react-router-dom';
import { useApp } from '../contexts/AppContext';

export const ProtectedRoute: React.FC<{ children: React.ReactNode }> = ({ children }) => {
  const { user } = useApp();

  if (!user) {
    return <Navigate to="/" replace />;
  }

  return <>{children}</>;
};
```

4. Update routes.tsx to protect routes:
```typescript
{
  path: '/projects',
  element: (
    <ProtectedRoute>
      <ProjectsView />
    </ProtectedRoute>
  ),
},
```

DELIVERABLE:
- Modular feature-based architecture
- React Router with proper URLs
- Protected routes
- Cleaner state management with Context
- Each feature is self-contained
- App.tsx is now <100 lines

